10:33 AM
deffo an opinion but i feel like a lot of ghost aus in fanfic specifically humanize the ghosts wayyy too much. like thats too be expected, bc u have these prewritten characters, u wanna do them justice and fit their personalities in there, etc etc but for me the draw of ghost stories is that element of the unknown. if the ghost is fully cognizant i usually lose interest. nobody in a ghost story should fully understand whats happening and why. and they should all be, on some level, desperate and scrabbling. u do not befriend a ghost. the same way u dont befriend the wreckage in the aftermath of a car crash, or the bones of a burned down house, or the slight depression in the soil where someone fell and did not get back up. you just see them and are filled with some emotion. and eventually you have to turn away from it. you know??
 (edited)

‚ú® Cook ‚ú® 2/17/2022 10:21 PM
In my desperate attempt to come up with why Fwhip goes by the title of Count despite by all means being a king in power, I have this idea: Gilded Helianthia, the Grimlands, Mythlands and the Crystal Cliffs all used to be part of one giant empire. Due to the empires large size, it would often position nobles as local rulers or instate local rulers as nobility in order to better rule the vast empire. The Counts of the Grimlands, were one of these families. The Grimlands wasn‚Äôt a particularly powerful or wealthy province, but it was incredibly important for the mining and extraction of redstone. Once this massive empire collapsed, the ruling family of the Grimlands kept their title of Count/Countess in legacy of the empire.
10:22 PM
Basically, keeping the title of Count shows their connection to this old empire, giving their rule ‚Äúlegitimacy.‚Äù (edited)

OOOO
‚ú® Cook ‚ú® 2/17/2022 10:27 PM
Mythland (kinda based on how much Sausage talked abt conquering in the early episodes) was more militaristic and concerned with expansion. A lot of their rulers wanted to recreate the old empire in the beginning, Mythlands capital itself being the capital of the old empire. For many years, they held Gilded Helianthia (then called Smallholdings) as a colony/territory that provided the kingdom with food. It was the breadbasket of the old empire as well. Mythlands old conquering ways have only rlly slowed down in recent generations, but military strength is still taught with a lot of pride to the average citizen and to their princes/princesses (edited)
‚ú® Cook ‚ú® 2/17/2022 10:39 PM
Now the Crystal Cliffs has always been a place of scholars and doctors and, due to their terrain, has always been more isolated even when part of the empire. The Crystal Cliffs doesn‚Äôt have a formal military and instead hires Pillagers to serve in a mercenary army. As of recent, the Grimlands has also provided soldiers to this informal army. Crystal Cliffs is fairly distrustful of other kingdoms, worried abt being dragged into their wars and fighting. I've heard he's in this server - wait, sorry, yeah, it's Underscore now, right?" Tubbo blinks, looking at the man in confusion - is that. Is he- is that really? No, it couldn't possibly be. But nobody has called him Tubbo Sparklez in such a long time. Even Wilbur never called him that - he was the one who helped Tubbo come up with the last name Underscore, actually, after he had been so resistant to the idea of 'Tubbo Minecraft'. And when even that had been too much for a younger Tubbo, Wilbur had taken on a different last name of his own - Soot. "Now neither of us have Phil's last name." He had said. Wilbur never called the man dad, only 'Phil'. Tubbo didn't call him dad either. "I- uh, yeah, of course I know Tubbo Underscore. He's me." The man, suddenly and without warning, engulfed Tubbo in a hug. "Uh, sorry, who- who are you?" The man sounded incredibly choked up. "Jordan." He said, his voice cracking.
